parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, including stalling, loss of power, and failure of essential systems, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Intermittent stalling
loss of power
failure of instrument panel indicators
windows rolling down on their own
doors not locking or unlocking
and failure of the keyless remote.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leaks from the sunroof can cause electrical malfunctions, damage to interior components, and reduced visibility while driving, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Water leaks from the sunroof
flooding of the interior
and electrical malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the door locks can prevent the driver or passengers from entering or exiting the vehicle, which can be a safety risk in emergency situations.
symptoms: Doors not locking or unlocking with the keyless remote or front/passenger door pads
and manual locking/unlocking required.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine and transmission failures can cause loss of power, stalling, and accidents.
symptoms: Engine stalling
loss of power
and transmission failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Battery drain and alternator failure can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Battery drain
alternator failure
and failure of the vehicle to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Light and License Plate Light Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake lights and license plate lights can increase the risk of accidents, as other drivers may not be aware of the vehicle's presence or actions.
symptoms: Brake lights and license plate lights not functioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump module can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Engine stalls
fuel odor inside or outside the vehicle
difficulty starting the engine
fuel leak from the top of the fuel tank
fuel spray from the fuel pump feed line
fuel odor in the garage or house.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel leak from the fuel tank can cause a fire hazard, especially when the vehicle is parked or driven, which can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Fuel odor inside or outside the vehicle
fuel leak from the top of the fuel tank
fuel spray from the fuel pump feed line
fuel odor in the garage or house.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A failure of the fuel system can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: Engine stalls
difficulty starting the engine
fuel odor inside or outside the vehicle
fuel leak from the top of the fuel tank
fuel spray from the fuel pump feed line.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or slows down without warning
the transmission fails to engage
or the vehicle is unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
or the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Driveshaft failure can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: A loud banging sound
the driveshaft comes loose
or the vehicle makes a terrible noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning
the vehicle slows down or loses power
or the vehicle is unable to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Wheel speed sensor malfunction can cause the vehicle's stability control system to malfunction, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The stability control light starts blinking
the vehicle's speed is limited
or the vehicle's traction control system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Crankshaft sensor failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning
the vehicle slows down or loses power
or the vehicle is unable to move.
